{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6e0f6e3b-d1bf-4016-b359-251aea8c338b","content":"The template is **functional but not fully publish-ready**. Here's what I found:\n\n**✅ Present & correct:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `sourceName`\n- `classifications`, `tags` (language + type)\n- `symbols` with a valid `Framework` choice parameter\n\n**⚠️ Missing recommended fields:**\n\n| Field | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | Enables editor validation/IntelliSense |\n| `description` | Critical for NuGet discoverability — users won't know what this template does |\n| `groupIdentity` | Needed to group template versions correctly in a NuGet pack |\n| `preferNameDirectory` | Standard for `project`-type templates (`true`) |\n\n**Verdict:** Add at minimum a `description` and `groupIdentity` before publishing. Without `description`, the template will appear blank on NuGet and in `dotnet new list`. Without `groupIdentity`, version upgrades won't replace the old template cleanly.\n\nWant me to add the missing fields?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3dbcaedd-9d96-42fe-a942-9bc63e490d61","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I can identify:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but highly recommended for validation and editor support. The standard value is `http://json.schemastore.org/template`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages so templates can be grouped properly across versions.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the same template are installed.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Not critical but good practice for project templates.\n\n\n5. **`defaultValue` references `net9.0`** — This works fine if you're targeting .NET 9.\n\n6. **Missing `description`** — While not strictly required by the engine, it's strongly recommended for discoverability on NuGet.\n\n7. **Missing `generatorVersions`** — Specifies which template engine version is required; recommended but not mandatory.\n\n8-11. **Core fields present** — `sourceName`, `identity`, `name`, and `shortName` are all in place, which is good.\n\n12. **`author` field** — Also present.\n\nLooking at the bigger picture, the template works functionally but has some gaps for publishing. Missing `$schema` for tooling support, no `description` for NuGet visibility, no `groupIdentity` for template packs, and no `preferNameDirectory` which is a best practice for project templates. It's usable as-is but not fully polished for distribution.","outputTokens":722,"requestId":"A7CA:36C28E:15F7E7F:188F21D:6A051F56"},"id":"da41f16e-0f22-48a9-8022-8e325678dc9d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:03:35.295Z","parentId":"ad63a8db-0a0e-4a28-bb3c-7124b308bfe8"}
